'''普韦布洛陶器'''是由当地的[[普韦布洛人|普韦布洛人]]及其祖先、美国西南部和墨西哥北部的祖传普韦布洛人和莫卧隆文化制作的[[陶瓷|陶瓷]]制品，已有近两千年的历史。<ref name="From This Earth">{{cite book |last1=Peckham |first1=Stewart |title=From This Earth: The Ancient Art of Pueblo Pottery |url=https://archive.org/details/fromthisearthanc00peck_0 |date=1990 |publisher=Museum of New Mexico Press |location=Santa Fe |isbn=08-9013-204-6}}</ref>大多数西南部的土著民族发展了陶器的传统，然而普韦布洛人在形状、大小和装饰方面更出色。圣塔克拉拉普韦布洛和圣伊尔德方索普韦布洛的现当代特瓦人喜欢用黑件工作，而阿科马普韦布洛说克里桑语的人和祖尼普韦布洛说马语的人工作时使用各种各样的颜色和设计主题。<ref name="NAIA book">{{cite book |last1=Furst |first1=Peter T. |last2=Furst |first2=Jill L. |title=North American Indian Art |url=https://archive.org/details/northamericanind00pete |date=1982 |publisher=Rizzoli |location=New York |isbn=0-8478-0461-5 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/northamericanind00pete/page/38 38]–40, 66–71}}</ref><ref name="Dillingham">{{cite book |last1=Dillingham |first1=Rick |title=Fourteen families in Pueblo pottery |date=1994 |publisher=University of New Mexico Press |location=Albuquerque |url=https://archive.org/details/fourteenfamilies0000dill |access-date=23 December 2020}}</ref>
